title: Filip Havelka
text:
Filip Havelka (born 21 January 1998) is a professional <a href="Czech%20Republic">Czech</a> <a href="Association%20football">football</a> <a href="midfielder">midfielder</a> currently playing for <a href="SK%20Dynamo%20%C4%8Cesk%C3%A9%20Bud%C4%9Bjovice">Dynamo České Budějovice</a> on loan from <a href="AC%20Sparta%20Prague">AC Sparta Prague</a> in the <a href="Czech%20First%20League">Czech First League</a>.
He made his senior league debut for Sparta Prague on 16 October 2016 in a <a href="Czech%20First%20League">Czech First League</a> 3–0 home win against <a href="FC%20Vyso%C4%8Dina%20Jihlava">Jihlava</a>. In July 2017, he went on loan to <a href="FC%20Slovan%20Liberec">Liberec</a>, another Czech First League side.
